5: Yet another scuffle in the East? *sigh*
7:
I already have my plate full dealing 
with the timber wolves' taxes, or lack 
thereof. I shan't stand for any more 
fudged documents.
9: Blast it all! What am I to tell Claudius?
12:
Lady Helga, with all due respect, you 
can't just—
Lady Helga!
16:
Albert! It's been too long.
...Remember me?
22:
Well old chap, I trust you know why I'm 
here! Let's get straight to business, 
shall we?
25:
Do I at least get a chance to explain 
myself first?
27:
Oh, certainly! Be my guest.
I'll just be filing my claws, don't mind 
me. Happen to like them SHARP, you 
see!
34:
Ahh, blood and steel. Smells like the 
right place!
41:
A canid? I didn't hear anythin' from the 
dogfolk 'bout a visitor.
44:
Oh? Why, if it isn't Whitetail. You've 
saved me the trouble of hunting you 
down.
45: You owe me, and I'm here to collect.
53: Nothin'! I've never seen her in my life!
57:
Allow me to introduce myself—Helga 
Vanese, charmed.
I WAS a soldier, until your escapades in 
the canyon put me out of a job.
59:
I've been itching for something to sink 
my teeth into... and I believe you can 
help with that!
63:
Not bad! Doing the Whitetail name 
proud, I see.
66:
Tch! The war's over! When're you guys 
gonna lay all those old grudges to 
rest?!
69:
Oh? Whatever do you mean? This has 
nothing to do with cats and dogs.
75:
And Albert! Poor puppy's been working 
ever so hard—I'd hate to spoil things 
for him.
79: Th-then what are you doing here?
82:
Well, I'm a soldier. A warrior. Not to 
toot my own horn, but if there's one 
thing I'm good at, it's hacking and 
whacking.
88:
Hah! Well, I'm a simple guy. You want 
a fight, I'll give you a fight!
90:
Oh, smells like the jig's up. Here he 
comes.
101:
Why, hello again, Albert! Took you 
longer that I thought, really.
104:
What do you think you're doing?! I was 
VERY clear that I would handle matters 
regarding your—
107:
Now, now, I believe I've just about 
sorted that out myself! I'm joining 
Whitetail's forces. Sounds like a perfect 
compromise for all, wouldn't you say?
116:
As I was just explaining, you put me 
out of a job, and I entirely expect you 
to put me back IN a job! Simple, right?
117:
I heard from Albert you and the 
Champion have got your paws full 
trying to combat some Lord of 
Shadow fellow.
119:
A bit over my head, to be quite frank, 
but it certainly sounds up my alley! 
You DO seem like quite a warrior 
yourself, I must say.
126:
Nimbus, I am terribly sorry. I tried to 
stop her...
128:
What do you say, Whitetail? Think you 
could pencil me in somewhere?
136:
Of course.
...Helga, welcome to Starview Village. 
I am its Keeper, Stella.
140:
There, now it's official. Also, one rule: 
don't call me "Whitetail." My name's 
Nimbus.
142: ...Other than that, suit yourself I guess.
147: Looking forward to working with you!
151:
Helga's among the dogfolk's best 
soldiers, but... Well, you saw how she is. 
She's not the type you can keep a tight 
leash on.
153:
I am honestly, sincerely, TERRIBLY sorry 
in advance.
157:
Hah! Hope she's got enough bite to 
back up her bark.
